        <h2>Case Study Â· Cyclistic</h2>
        <p>How members and casual riders use the bike-share differently and which marketing actions can increase conversions to annual plans.</p>
        <div class="kpis">
          <div class="kpi"><span class="muted tiny">Period</span><b>Q1 2019â€“2020</b></div>
          <div class="kpi"><span class="muted tiny">Tools</span><b>Excel Â· R Â· Tableau</b></div>
          <div class="kpi"><span class="muted tiny">Focus</span><b>Behavior & Conversion</b></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Key findings</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Members concentrate on weekdays (commute pattern); casual riders are stronger on weekends.</li>
          <li>Casual rides are longer on average; membersâ€™ trips are shorter and more consistent.</li>
          <li>Peaks: members 7â€“9 & 16â€“18; casual late morning/afternoon.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Recommendations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Weekend pass â†’ annual upgrade with progressive discount for repeat casuals.</li>
          <li>In-app/kiosk prompts in high-casual stations showing value of the annual plan after N rides/month.</li>
          <li>Commute-value campaign near transit hubs during 7â€“9 and 16â€“18.</li>
        </ul>

